# Build context exclusions for `docker build`.
#
# Without this file `COPY . /workspace/sparkle` ships
# `.lake/` (~8 GB of compiled oleans + native objects)
# into every image — adding ~3 minutes per build and
# guaranteeing the cache layer changes on every Lean
# build, defeating Lake's own caching.
#
# We exclude the heavy build artefacts and let the
# Dockerfile's `lake update` / `lake build` step rebuild
# them inside the image, which is what we want anyway
# (build artefacts must match the container's toolchain).

# Lake build artefacts (regenerated by `lake build`).
.lake/

# Tutorial generated artefacts (regenerated by
# `bash docs/tutorial/build-from-md.sh`).
docs/tutorial/Notebooks/Gen/

# Verilator obj_dir trees (re-generated as needed).
verilator/obj_dir/
verilator/obj_dir_notrace/
verilator/*.so

# Editor / OS junk.
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# Local docker volume mounts.
.docker-cache/

# Playwright e2e artefacts (regenerated by `npm install` and the
# Playwright runner — not part of the image build).
tests/e2e/node_modules/
tests/e2e/playwright-report/
tests/e2e/test-results/
